name: Sewaddle
flavorText: Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

name: Swadloon
flavorText: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Leavanny
flavorText: Upon finding a small Pokemon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using cutters on its arms and sticky silk.
Ability1Text: Each of your Pokemon that has any Energy attached to it has no Weakness.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

name: Petilil
flavorText: Since they prefer moist, nutrient-rich soil, the areas where Petilil live are known to be good for growing plants.
Attack2Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Lilligant
flavorText: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect. It withers if a Trainer does not take good care of it.
Attack1Text: Heal all damage from 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Dwebble
flavorText: The Pokemon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks during your opponent's next turn.

name: Crustle
flavorText: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 more damage.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Karrablast
flavorText: When they feel threatened, they spit acidic liquid to drive attackers away. This Pokemon targets Shelmet.
Attack1Text: If Shelmet is in play, search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokemon and put it onto this Pokemon. (This counts as evolving this Pokemon.) Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Foongus
flavorText: For some reason, this Pokemon resembles a Poke Ball. They release poison spores to repel those who try to catch them.

name: Amoonguss
flavorText: They show off their Poke Ball caps to lure prey, but very few Pokemon are fooled by this.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned. Put 2 damage counters instead of 1 on that Pokemon between turns.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Shelmet
flavorText: It evolves when bathed in an electric-like energy along with Karrablast. The reason is still unknown.
Attack1Text: If Karrablast is in play, search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokemon and put it onto this Pokemon. (This counts as evolving this Pokemon.) Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Accelgor
flavorText: Having removed its heavy shell, it becomes very light and can fight with ninja-like movements.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon can't use Slashing Strike during your next turn.

name: Virizion
flavorText: Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Leaf Wallop attack does 40 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Victini
flavorText: This Pokemon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, after you flip any coins for an attack, you may ignore all effects of those coin flips and being flipping those coins again. You can't use more than 1 Victory Star Ability each turn.
Attack1Text: Move all Energy attached to this Pokemon to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Victini
flavorText: This Pokemon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.
Attack1Text: If you have 4 or fewer Benched Pokemon, this attack does nothing.

name: Pansear
flavorText: This Pokemon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600Â° F.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Simisear
flavorText: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 80 damage times the number of heads.

name: Heatmor
flavorText: Using their very hot, flame-covered tongues, they burn through Durant's steel bodies and consume their insides.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: Before doing damage, discard a Pokemon Tool card attached to the Defending Pokemon.

name: Larvesta
flavorText: This Pokemon was believed to have been born from the sun. When it evolves, its entire body is engulfed in flames.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, discard an Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Larvesta
flavorText: The base of volcanoes is where they make their homes. They shoot fire from their five horns to repel attacking enemies.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Volcarona
flavorText: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona's fire provided a replacement for the sun.
Attack1Text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokemon.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Tympole
flavorText: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.

name: Palpitoad
flavorText: It lives in water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to capture prey.
Attack2Text: Does 20 damage times the number of your Pokemon that have the Round attack.

name: Seismitoad
flavorText: It increases the power of its punches by vibrating the bumps on its fists. It can turn a boulder to rubble with one punch.
Attack1Text: Does 30 damage times the number of your Pokemon that have the Round attack.

name: Tirtouga
flavorText: Restored from a fossil, this Pokemon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.

name: Carracosta
flavorText: They can live both in the ocean and on land. A slap from one of them is enough to open a hole in the bottom of a tanker.
Ability1Text: If any damage is done to this Pokemon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, reduce that damage by 50 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon.

name: Vanillite
flavorText: This Pokemon formed from icicles bathed in energy from the morning sun. It sleeps buried in snow.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Vanillish
flavorText: It conceals itself from enemy eyes by creating many small ice particles and hiding among them.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Vanilluxe
flavorText: If both heads get angry simultaneously, this Pokemon expels a blizzard, burying everything in snow.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads. If either of them is heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Frillish
flavorText: With its thin, veil-like arms wrapped around the body of its opponent, it sinks to the ocean floor.

name: Jellicent
flavorText: The fate of ships and crew that wander into Jellicent's habitats: all sunken, all lost, all vanished.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is your Active Pokemon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if this Pokemon is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack1Text: Does 20 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Cryogonal
flavorText: They are born in snow clouds. They use chains made of ice crystals to capture prey.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon is a Fighting Pokemon, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Cryogonal
flavorText: They are born in snow clouds. They use chains made of ice crystals to capture prey.
Attack1Text: Switch the Defending Pokemon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: You may return this Pokemon and all cards attached to it to your hand.

name: Kyurem
flavorText: It generates powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.
Attack1Text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Blitzle
flavorText: When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokemon during your opponent's next turn.

name: Zebstrika
flavorText: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, discard all Lightning Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Emolga
flavorText: They live on treetops and glide using the inside of a cape-like membrane while discharging electricity.
Attack1Text: Does 20 more damage if you have any Lightning Pokemon on your Bench.

name: Tynamo
flavorText: While one alone doesn't have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Tynamo
flavorText: While one alone doesn't have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

name: Eelektrik
flavorText: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Lightning Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Eelektross
flavorText: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Stunfisk
flavorText: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokemon does 30 damage to itself.

name: Victini
flavorText: It creates an unlimited supply of energy inside its body, which it shares with those who touch it.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. If either of them is tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Yamask
flavorText: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Yamask
flavorText: These Pokemon arose from the spirits of people interred in graves in past ages. Each retains memories of its former life.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Cofagrigus
flavorText: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.
Attack1Text: Move all damage counters from 1 of your Benched Pokemon to the Defending Pokemon.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Cofagrigus
flavorText: They pretend to be elaborate coffins to teach lessons to grave robbers. Their bodies are covered in pure gold.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, flip a coin. If heads, this Pokemon is not Knocked Out and its remaining HP becomes 10 instead.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Trubbish
flavorText: The combination of garbage bags and industrial waste caused the chemical reaction that created this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Put a card from your discard pile on top of your deck.

name: Garbodor
flavorText: They absorb garbage and make it part of their bodies. They shoot poisonous liquid from their right-hand fingertips.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Solosis
flavorText: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

name: Duosion
flavorText: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.

name: Reuniclus
flavorText: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 5 cards of your deck and put them back on top of your deck in any order.
Attack2Text: Does 40 damage times the number of Reuniclus you have in play.

name: Reuniclus
flavorText: These remarkably intelligent Pokemon fight by controlling arms that can grip with rock-crushing power.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Elgyem
flavorText: This Pokemon had never been seen until it appeared from far in the desert 50 years ago.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Elgyem
flavorText: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent's brain, causing unendurable headaches.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for 2 Basic Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Beheeyem
flavorText: It uses psychic power to control an opponent's brain and tamper with its memories.
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon that shares a type with the Defending Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Litwick
flavorText: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokemon, which becomes the fuel it burns.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Litwick
flavorText: While shining a light and pretending to be a guide, it leaches off the life force of any who follow it.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Lampent
flavorText: This ominous Pokemon is feared. Through cities it wanders, searching for the spirits of the fallen.
Attack1Text: Switch the Defending Pokemon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.

name: Chandelure
flavorText: It absorbs a spirit, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokemon is your Active Pokemon, you may put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Pokemon in any way you like.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Burned and Confused.

name: Gigalith
flavorText: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon for each Fighting Energy attached to this Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Timburr
flavorText: It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle the lumber without difficulty.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Gurdurr
flavorText: This Pokemon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Conkeldurr
flavorText: It it thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2,000 years ago.
Ability1Text: This Pokemon gets +20 HP for each Fighting Energy attached to it.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Conkeldurr
flavorText: They use concrete pillars as walking canes. They know moves that enable them to swing the pillars freely in battle.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on the Defending Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

name: Archen
flavorText: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokemon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

name: Archeops
flavorText: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.
Ability1Text: Each play can't play any Pokemon from his or her hand to evolve his or her Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Does 10 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Stunfisk
flavorText: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a volt of electricity.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Mienfoo
flavorText: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attack. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.

name: Mienshao
flavorText: It wield the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arms attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot even be seen.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Golett
flavorText: These Pokemon are thought to have been created by the science of an ancient and mysterious civilization.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage and the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Golurk
flavorText: It is said that Golurk were ordered to protect people and Pokemon by the ancient people who made them.
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

name: Terrakion
flavorText: Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokemon is spoken of in legends.
Attack1Text: If any of your Pokemon were Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack during his or her last turn, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Landorus
flavorText: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as "The Guardian of the Fields."
Attack1Text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Does 10 damage to each Benched Pokemon (both yours and your opponent's). (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Pawniard
flavorText: They fight at Bisharp's command. They cling to their prey and inflict damage by sinking their blades into it.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Bisharp
flavorText: Bisharp pursues prey in the company of a large group of Pawniard. Then Bisharp finishes off the prey.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokemon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 50 more damage.
Attack2Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Deino
flavorText: They cannot see, so they tackle and bite to learn about their surroundings. Their bodies are covered in wounds.

name: Zweilous
flavorText: Since their two heads do not get along and compete with each other for food, they always eat too much.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

name: Hydreigon
flavorText: The heads on their arms do not have brains. They use all three heads to consume and destroy everything.
Ability1Text: All Energy attached to this Pokemon are Darkness Energy instead of their usual type.
Attack1Text: Does 40 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Escavalier
flavorText: These Pokemon evolve by wearing the shell covering of a Shelmet. The steel armor protects their whole body.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokemon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 70 damage times the number of heads.

name: Pawniard
flavorText: Blades comprise this Pokemon's entire body. If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.

name: Bisharp
flavorText: It leads a group of Pawniard. It battles to become the boss, but will be driven from the group if it loses.
Attack1Text: Attach a Metal Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Does 20 more damage for each Metal Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Durant
flavorText: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves against Heatmor.
Attack1Text: For each of your Durant in play, discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Cobalion
flavorText: It has a body and heart of steel. Its glare is sufficient to make even an unruly Pokemon obey it.
Attack1Text: Does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Audino
flavorText: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.
Attack1Text: Does 10 damage times the number of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Axew
flavorText: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Fraxure
flavorText: Since a broken tusk will not grow back, they diligently sharpen their tusks on river rocks after they've been fighting.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

name: Haxorus
flavorText: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon can't attack during your next turn.

name: Druddigon
flavorText: It races through narrow caves, using its sharp claws to catch prey. The skin on its face is harder than a rock.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is your Active Pokemon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if this Pokemon is Knocked Out), put 2 damage counters on the Attacking Pokemon.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Virizion
flavorText: Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Leaf Wallop attack does 40 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Victini
flavorText: This Pokemon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, after you flip any coins for an attack, you may ignore all effects of those coin flips and being flipping those coins again. You can't use more than 1 Victory Star Ability each turn.
Attack1Text: Move all Energy attached to this Pokemon to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Terrakion
flavorText: Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokemon is spoken of in legends.
Attack1Text: If any of your Pokemon were Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack during his or her last turn, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Cobalion
flavorText: It has a body and heart of steel. Its glare is sufficient to make even an unruly Pokemon obey it.
Attack1Text: Does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Meowth
flavorText: This is an extremely rare Meowth card. Maybe good fortune will come to you if you hold this card!
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.
Attack2Text: Draw a card.
